    36→    36→- `cooperative`: Scroll pans page; Ctrl+scroll zooms map
    37→    37→- `greedy`: Scroll always zooms map
    38→    38→- `none`: Disable interactions
    39→    39→
    40→    40→**Camera Easing:** Google uses `Quadratic.Out` easing with tween.js for smooth camera transitions. Typical duration: 300-500ms for zoom, 15s for animated tours.
    41→    41→
    42→    42→**Momentum Physics:**
    43→    43→- Pan has momentum/inertia after release
    44→    44→- Zoom does NOT have momentum (intentional UX decision)
    45→    45→- Friction coefficient creates natural deceleration
    46→    46→
    47→    47→### 1.3 Apple Maps / iOS
    48→    48→
    49→    49→| Gesture | Action | Notes |
    50→    50→|---------|--------|-------|
    51→    51→| One-finger drag | Pan with strong momentum | "Buttery" feel |
    52→    52→| Pinch | Zoom with momentum | Unlike Google Maps |
    53→    53→| Double-tap | Zoom in | Fixed 2x increment |
    54→    54→| Two-finger tap | Zoom out | Fixed 0.5x increment |
    55→    55→| Rotate gesture | Rotate map | Optional feature |
    56→    56→
    57→    57→**Key Differentiator:** iOS implements momentum for BOTH pan AND zoom gestures, creating a more fluid feel than Google Maps.
    58→    58→
    59→    59→### 1.4 Canva
    60→    60→
    61→    61→| Gesture | Action | Notes |
    62→    62→|---------|--------|-------|
    63→    63→| Drag | Pan canvas | Infinite canvas |
    64→    64→| Scroll wheel | Zoom | Centers on cursor |
    65→    65→| Pinch | Zoom | Touch devices |
    66→    66→| Pan gesture | Pan | Two-finger drag |
    67→    67→
    68→    68→**Infinite Canvas:** Canva's whiteboard feature supports unlimited pan in all directions with zoom/pan/scroll navigation.
    69→    69→
