   467→   467→
   468→   468→## 6. Cross-Platform Considerations
   469→   469→
   470→   470→### 6.1 macOS vs Windows Scroll Direction
   471→   471→
   472→   472→| Platform | Default Scroll Direction |
   473→   473→|----------|--------------------------|
   474→   474→| macOS (trackpad) | "Natural" (content follows fingers) |
   475→   475→| macOS (mouse) | Same as trackpad (unless changed) |
   476→   476→| Windows | "Traditional" (opposite of macOS) |
   477→   477→| Linux | Varies by desktop environment |
   478→   478→
   479→   479→**Recommendation:** Use the raw `deltaY` value directly. Browser vendors have already normalized for user preferences. Do NOT attempt to detect or reverse scroll direction.
   480→   480→
   481→   481→### 6.2 Platform-Specific deltaY Magnitude
   482→   482→
   483→   483→| Platform | Typical deltaY (mouse) | Typical deltaY (trackpad) |
   484→   484→|----------|------------------------|---------------------------|
   485→   485→| Windows Chrome | 100 | 1-10 (many events) |
   486→   486→| macOS Chrome | 100 | 0.5-3 (many events) |
   487→   487→| Windows Firefox | 3 (LINE mode) | 1-2 |
   488→   488→| macOS Safari | 12-30 | 0.5-2 |
   489→   489→
   490→   490→### 6.3 Recommended Normalization Strategy
   491→   491→
   492→   492→```typescript
   493→   493→const ZOOM_SENSITIVITY = 0.001;  // Base sensitivity
   494→   494→const MAX_ZOOM_DELTA = 0.5;      // Cap per event
   495→   495→
   496→   496→function calculateZoomDelta(event: WheelEvent): number {
   497→   497→  let delta = event.deltaY;
   498→   498→
   499→   499→  // Normalize LINE mode to pixels
   500→   500→  if (event.deltaMode === 1) {
   501→   501→    delta *= 16; // Approximate line height
   502→   502→  }
   503→   503→
   504→   504→  // Apply sensitivity and clamp
   505→   505→  delta *= ZOOM_SENSITIVITY;
   506→   506→  delta = Math.max(-MAX_ZOOM_DELTA, Math.min(MAX_ZOOM_DELTA, delta));
   507→   507→
   508→   508→  return delta;
   509→   509→}
   510→   510→```
